<PageLayout title="SSA Berkeley | Leadership">
    <section class="header">
        <div>
            <h1>Our Executive Committee</h1>
            <p>
                As leaders of the organization, the Executive Committee (EXCO)
                is fully committed to foster a welcoming, inclusive, supportive,
                and happy SSA community!
            </p>
        </div>
        <Image
            src={team}
            alt="SSA EXCO 2024-25"
            style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 500px; min-width: 200px; border-radius: 1rem;"
            loading="eager"
        />
    </section>

    <section class="currEXCO">
        <div class="profile">
            <Image
                src={aadil}
                alt="Aadil Jamari"
                style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 400px; min-width: 150px; border-radius: 1rem;"
            />
            <div class="data">
                <h1>Aadil Jamari</h1>
                <h2>President</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                Aadil always has the tea, and is always willing to spill if you
                ask. When he's not spilling it, you can find him exploring new
                foods in Berkeley or trying his best at what he calls "singing".
                Aadil is also an aspiring trilingual: he can speak English,
                Malay and is currently learning Mandarin Chinese at Berkeley!
                Unfortunately, his hottest take in Cal is that bubble tea is
                severely overrated. He would much rather drink the cans of Milo
                he has stockpiled instead.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="profile">
            <Image
                src={nyx}
                alt="Nyx Iskandar"
                style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 400px; min-width: 150px; border-radius: 1rem;"
            />
            <div class="data">
                <h1>Nyx Iskandar</h1>
                <h2>Vice President</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                Nyx aspires to be Tony Stark, minus the playboy stuff ;D. She
                loves to code cool and impactful projects for the community, one
                of them being this very website! To compensate for all the
                sitting down, she plays volleyball and boulders, so you'll see
                her a lot at RSF and Benchmark Climbing (protip: don't go to
                Mosaic). She's also a STRONG proponent of physical notebooks
                over iPads and laptops (that's her way of reconnecting with
                nature, at least the processed version of it oops).
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="profile">
            <Image
                src={shawn}
                alt="Shawn Goh"
                style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 400px; min-width: 150px; border-radius: 1rem;"
            />
            <div class="data">
                <h1>Shawn Goh</h1>
                <h2>Treasurer</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                Shawn loves everything outdoors (esp the beach), sports, and
                failing to plan stuff. If you want to talk about random trivia
                or the environment (or just escape sweaty CS/DS/Econ talk), feel
                free to reach out. Shawn is a pro at doing nothing but
                unfortunately struggles to inspire others to do the same. If you
                ever bump into him on campus, feel special, because he is a
                super-rare pokemon!
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="profile">
            <Image
                src={ice}
                alt="Ice Kulruchakorn"
                style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 400px; min-width: 150px; border-radius: 1rem;"
            />
            <div class="data">
                <h1>Ice Kulruchakorn</h1>
                <h2>Head of Events & Publicity</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                Ice will tell you that she served in NS upon the first 10
                minutes of meeting you (no one knows if she actually did). If
                you see her on campus, she's probably speedwalking to class or
                appreciating the pretty California sunset. She's always down to
                talk about award-winning movies, the political state of the
                world, or why New York is better than SF.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="profile">
            <Image
                src={kenny}
                alt="Kenny Wongchamcharoen"
                style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 400px; min-width: 150px; border-radius: 1rem;"
            />
            <div class="data">
                <h1>Kenny Wongchamcharoen</h1>
                <h2>Head of External</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                Kenny is an adventurous soul who loves nothing more than
                travelling to new places and hiking: whether it's narrowly
                escaping a fall off an Oregon cliff or an unexpected dash away
                from trouble on the Chicago 'L' station at night. When he's not
                out exploring, you can find him belting out tunes with his a
                cappella group and hitting the tennis courts (though he has lost
                to just about everyone). Kenny's love for spicy laksa is almost
                as much as his notoriously low alcohol tolerance.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="profile">
            <Image
                src={ethan}
                alt="Ethan Lau"
                style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 400px; min-width: 150px; border-radius: 1rem;"
            />
            <div class="data">
                <h1>Ethan Lau</h1>
                <h2>Deputy Head of Events & Publicity</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                Ethan is always down for spontaneous trips anywhere. Being
                permanently nocturnal (as a result of a permanent state of
                procrastination), you will always find him at any of Berkeley's
                many eating places that are still open at 2 in the morning. Hit
                him up if you want to talk ðŸ™‚
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="profile">
            <Image
                src={yinqi}
                alt="Yi Yinqi"
                style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 400px; min-width: 150px; border-radius: 1rem;"
            />
            <div class="data">
                <h1>Yi Yinqi</h1>
                <h2>Deputy Head of External</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                Yinqi is a pro at procrastination: she has perfected the art of
                avoiding work until the eleventh hour and is always seen
                navigating through homework in panic before its deadline. Yinqi
                thrives in her cozy indoor haven and is often found savoring
                boba with friends. If you want an ego boost in any sports, Yinqi
                is your go-to challenger!
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

